WEBVTT

00:00.334 --> 00:02.918
<i>Previously on "scandal"...</i>
This next lady says
her husband worked

00:02.919 --> 00:05.503
For a super-secret spy agency
operating outside the command

00:05.506 --> 00:06.705
Of the united states
government.

00:06.707 --> 00:08.123
Called b613.

00:08.124 --> 00:09.540
You need to shut this down,
rosen -- now.

00:09.543 --> 00:11.377
I'm not gonna
shut it down.
What?

00:11.379 --> 00:13.445
You gave me those files.
You said, "go get the bad guys."

00:13.447 --> 00:15.614
I'm going to get
the bad guys.

00:15.616 --> 00:19.451
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

00:19.453 --> 00:20.552
Jake: What's this?

00:20.554 --> 00:22.354
David:
An immunity agreement.

00:22.356 --> 00:24.523
You agree to testify
against command,

00:24.525 --> 00:27.026
And the government
will never prosecute you.

00:27.028 --> 00:29.495
You think i'm gonna testify
against command

00:29.497 --> 00:30.729
And help bring down b613?

00:30.731 --> 00:33.332
I also have huck and quinn,
even charlie,

00:33.334 --> 00:34.299
But i need you.

00:34.301 --> 00:35.534
You are the big fish.

00:35.536 --> 00:37.669
You worked for rowan.
You stood in his shoes.

00:37.671 --> 00:39.471
You know where the bodies
are buried.

00:39.473 --> 00:41.273
Be a witness,
and we can make our case now.

00:41.275 --> 00:43.142
We won't need
any other agents.
I can't.

00:43.144 --> 00:46.412
This is my death warrant,
you understand?

00:46.414 --> 00:50.082
I sign this, i die.
We're all gonna die, rosen.

00:50.084 --> 00:52.351
No. I'm out.

00:52.353 --> 00:54.270
I'm done.

00:54.271 --> 00:56.188
White hats, jake.
We are the good guys.

00:56.190 --> 00:58.557
We get justice
no matter what.

00:58.559 --> 00:59.825
Goodbye, rosen.

00:59.827 --> 01:02.394
If you don't testify,
i can't protect you, jake.

01:04.398 --> 01:06.732
Is that a threat?

01:06.734 --> 01:09.735
We are taking down command,
and you were once command, too.

01:18.345 --> 01:20.095
Hey!

01:20.096 --> 01:21.846
I don't need protection
from you, rosen.

01:21.849 --> 01:24.583
<i>You</i> need protection
from<i> me.</i>

01:24.585 --> 01:28.087
Drop this case
or i'll drop it for you.

01:42.269 --> 01:46.705
Hey. Change of plans.

01:46.707 --> 01:48.640
[ bill withers'
"grandma's hands" plays ]

01:52.213 --> 01:54.446
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

01:56.117 --> 02:02.421
¶ grandma's hands clapped
in church on sunday morning ¶

02:02.423 --> 02:07.860
¶ grandma's hands played
a tambourine so well ¶

02:07.862 --> 02:13.198
¶ grandma's hands
used to issue out a warning ¶

02:13.200 --> 02:16.902
¶ she'd say, "billy,
don't you run so fast ¶

02:16.904 --> 02:19.805
¶ might fall on
a piece of glass ¶

02:19.807 --> 02:21.240
¶ might be snakes there
in that grass" ¶

02:21.242 --> 02:22.274
Charlie?

02:22.276 --> 02:23.909
Max.

02:23.911 --> 02:25.677
Long time, no see.

02:25.679 --> 02:26.778
Max butler.

02:26.780 --> 02:28.964
Retired b613.

02:28.965 --> 02:31.149
Worked with jake ballard
in syria in the late '90s.

02:31.152 --> 02:32.918
Max and jake killed
six lebanese agents together,

02:32.920 --> 02:34.853
Butchered them
in a bath house in damascus.

02:34.855 --> 02:36.305
Good gig -- damascus.

02:36.306 --> 02:37.756
Sure, the weather's dry,
but the girls...
Charlie.

02:37.758 --> 02:38.757
Sorry.<i> Women.</i>

02:38.759 --> 02:40.792
We need max.

02:40.794 --> 02:43.362
¶ grandma's hands used to lift
her face and tell her ¶

02:43.364 --> 02:44.596
Hello, margot.

02:44.598 --> 02:47.766
Margot ross
worked closely with jake

02:47.768 --> 02:50.302
During several missions
in southeast asia after 9/11.

02:50.304 --> 02:52.304
We need her,
and we need simon.

02:52.306 --> 02:54.706
¶ "put yourself
in jesus' hands" ¶

02:54.708 --> 02:55.707
¶ grandma's hands ¶

02:55.709 --> 02:57.676
Simon?

02:57.678 --> 02:58.944
Who the hell
are you?

02:58.946 --> 03:01.713
I'm quinn.
Can we talk?

03:01.715 --> 03:05.817
Jake worked under simon
in europe from 2003-2007.

03:05.819 --> 03:08.220
They're credited
with 37 assassinations

03:08.222 --> 03:10.422
From hamburg to grenada.
Yeah, but some of those
were bombings.

03:10.424 --> 03:11.857
So?
So, that's cheating.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.926
Murder is murder.
Back me up here, big guy.

03:13.928 --> 03:16.361
No, bombings
are cheating.
Listen, here's the plan --

03:16.363 --> 03:18.830
We pull in these three agents,
gain their trust.

03:18.832 --> 03:20.599
What's your offer?

03:20.600 --> 03:22.367
We offer them full immunity
from prosecution.

03:22.369 --> 03:25.204
Immunity from<i> every</i> mission?
Domestic and international?

03:25.206 --> 03:26.238
All of it.

03:26.240 --> 03:27.472
Put them in a safe house

03:27.474 --> 03:29.541
Until i can convene
a secret grand jury,

03:29.543 --> 03:32.678
And we have ourselves
an airtight case.

03:32.680 --> 03:34.613
<i>That's how we bring in</i>
<i>jake ballard.</i>

03:34.615 --> 03:36.248
<i>He's on the hook.</i>

03:36.249 --> 03:37.882
<i>So, we offer him immunity,</i>
<i>get him to testify.</i>

03:37.885 --> 03:40.385
<i>Once he's in,</i>
<i>other agents will step forward,</i>

03:40.387 --> 03:44.423
<i>And that's how we take down</i>
<i>b613 for good.</i>

03:54.969 --> 03:56.768
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

04:01.942 --> 04:05.844
Russell: You shout...
In your sleep.

04:06.914 --> 04:09.815
About a red door and a ring
in other languages.

04:09.817 --> 04:11.650
You have to go.

04:11.652 --> 04:12.985
French, russian,
farsi, mandarin,

04:12.987 --> 04:14.586
And i want to say...
Swahili?

04:14.588 --> 04:15.520
Zulu?

04:15.522 --> 04:16.455
Both.

04:16.457 --> 04:17.489
Listen, russell --

04:17.491 --> 04:19.625
My name's
not really russell.

04:19.627 --> 04:21.893
I mean, it is,
but it's franklin --

04:21.895 --> 04:23.962
Franklin russell.

04:23.964 --> 04:26.765
You gave me a fake name.

04:26.767 --> 04:29.501
You have a problem
with that, alex?
[ laughs ]

04:29.503 --> 04:31.270
Are we sticking with alex, or
can i start calling you olivia?

04:31.272 --> 04:33.038
Um, well, you don't need

04:33.040 --> 04:36.441
To call me anything
because this is it.

04:36.443 --> 04:38.443
Well, here's the thing,
alex --

04:38.445 --> 04:40.846
I don't think it is.

04:44.451 --> 04:46.885
[ cellphone rings ]

04:46.887 --> 04:49.421
Hello?

04:49.423 --> 04:51.356
Yes.

04:51.358 --> 04:54.926
I'll be right there.

04:54.928 --> 04:57.229
It's not too late.

04:57.230 --> 04:59.531
Congressman, i'd like to believe
that's true. However --

04:59.533 --> 05:01.600
But you don't, and you think
my father's guilty.

05:01.602 --> 05:02.968
This isn't about
what i believe.

05:02.970 --> 05:05.404
I don't know what you think
i could do at this point.

05:05.406 --> 05:06.672
If you'd heard him...

05:06.674 --> 05:09.041
You can't imagine.

05:09.043 --> 05:11.843
I was in my room
when he found her,

05:11.845 --> 05:13.078
Found jamie...

05:13.080 --> 05:15.914
Hanging from a rod
in her closet.

05:15.916 --> 05:16.882
15 years old.

05:16.884 --> 05:20.719
The screams, the sobbing.

05:20.721 --> 05:22.821
I thought
it was a neighbor's kid

05:22.823 --> 05:24.022
Or some kind of animal.

05:24.024 --> 05:27.559
The look on his face.

05:27.561 --> 05:30.028
The sounds coming from him
as he cut her down

05:30.030 --> 05:31.997
And tried over and over

05:31.999 --> 05:35.534
To beat the life
back into her lungs.

05:37.338 --> 05:39.938
When the police found
jamie's diary

05:39.940 --> 05:42.407
And told him
why she killed herself --

05:42.409 --> 05:44.910
Because that piece of crap
broke her heart.

05:44.912 --> 05:46.878
Her math teacher.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.880
She was 14 when things started
between them --

05:48.882 --> 05:49.981
14.

05:49.983 --> 05:52.718
He was 29.
Can you imagine?

05:52.720 --> 05:55.587
My father had every reason
in the world to do him harm,

05:55.589 --> 05:56.888
But he didn't.
I know it.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.457
What do you
think happened

05:58.459 --> 06:00.292
When your father
went to confront him?

06:00.294 --> 06:01.860
Last night, around 9:00,

06:01.862 --> 06:04.996
I grabbed the gun i keep hidden
behind my bedside table,

06:04.998 --> 06:07.666
A box of bullets
from the drawer there.

06:07.668 --> 06:10.769
Drove to the home of dan hoffman
and rang the bell.

06:10.771 --> 06:12.838
When that bastard
came to the door,

06:12.840 --> 06:15.874
I pointed the gun at his chest
and shot him twice.

06:15.876 --> 06:17.008
Maybe three times.

06:17.010 --> 06:19.211
Should have been more.

06:19.212 --> 06:21.413
Should have emptied the entire
gun in that son of a bitch.

06:21.415 --> 06:22.080
But i didn't.

06:22.082 --> 06:23.749
Went home.
End of story.

06:23.751 --> 06:26.818
Tanner: That chilling confession
by george reed was recorded

06:26.820 --> 06:28.954
In the selbyville, delaware,
police station

06:28.956 --> 06:31.423
15 years ago,
almost to the day.

06:31.425 --> 06:34.926
President grant rejected pleas
from george reed's son,

06:34.928 --> 06:36.094
Congressman nicholas reed,

06:36.096 --> 06:38.029
To pressure
the governor of delaware

06:38.031 --> 06:39.898
To issue a stay
in the execution,

06:39.900 --> 06:41.850
Which is set for next month.

06:41.851 --> 06:43.801
Sure, the president sympathizes
with congressman reed.

06:43.804 --> 06:46.104
He also sympathizes
with the victim in this case

06:46.106 --> 06:48.540
And the right
of the state of delaware

06:48.542 --> 06:50.842
To handle their own
justice system independently.

06:50.844 --> 06:52.377
Next question.

06:52.378 --> 06:53.911
Tanner: Congressman reed
has fought tirelessly

06:53.914 --> 06:56.415
Over the last 15 years to
reverse his father's conviction.

06:56.417 --> 06:57.649
But tonight,
that long struggle

06:57.651 --> 06:59.951
To spare his father
from execution

06:59.953 --> 07:02.487
Has clearly come to an end.

07:02.489 --> 07:04.656
I have no idea
why he confessed,

07:04.658 --> 07:07.926
Why he still, to this day,
stands by that confession.

07:07.928 --> 07:09.628
Maybe he wishes
he killed the guy.

07:09.630 --> 07:10.829
I just -- i-i don't know.

07:10.831 --> 07:13.098
Again, congressman,
i'm sorry,

07:13.100 --> 07:16.067
But i don't know
what i can help with.

07:16.069 --> 07:19.004
Just, please, olivia,
meet with him.

07:19.006 --> 07:21.706
I promise you'll see.

07:21.708 --> 07:24.910
I'm not just a son
with a serious case of denial.

07:24.912 --> 07:28.113
My father is innocent.
He did not shoot dan hoffman.

07:28.115 --> 07:30.916
You're my last hope
for proving that.

07:33.854 --> 07:36.721
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

07:36.723 --> 07:39.224
So, i just have a few more
questions, and then we're done.

07:39.226 --> 07:41.927
You own your own...
You make soap?

07:41.929 --> 07:43.929
Yeah,
i got a little soap company.

07:43.931 --> 07:45.914
Little.

07:45.915 --> 07:47.898
It's not wal-mart or anything,
but it does okay.

07:47.901 --> 07:49.901
And the books are clean.

07:49.903 --> 07:50.869
[ chuckles ]

07:50.871 --> 07:52.571
Soap books are clean.

07:52.573 --> 07:56.575
[ laughs ]
i just thought of that.

07:56.577 --> 07:57.709
Get it?

07:57.711 --> 07:59.678
Uh-huh.

07:59.680 --> 08:01.880
Okay. What else
do you want to ask me?

08:01.882 --> 08:03.615
Do you agree
with her politics?

08:03.617 --> 08:04.816
I love her politics.

08:04.818 --> 08:07.252
I'm also crazy
about her husband's.

08:07.254 --> 08:11.490
He<i> used</i> to be a republican,
but that's not her fault.

08:11.492 --> 08:12.157
[ chuckles ]

08:12.159 --> 08:14.142
What else?

08:14.143 --> 08:16.126
Uh, when was the last time
you went to church?

08:16.129 --> 08:18.797
You are down south, honey.
You are in church right now.

08:18.799 --> 08:19.831
[ chuckles ]

08:19.833 --> 08:21.266
I think
that's everything i need.

08:21.268 --> 08:23.768
Harmony, it has been a pleasure
chatting with you.

08:23.770 --> 08:25.804
I know mellie appreciates you
taking the time.

08:25.806 --> 08:27.806
How is she?

08:27.808 --> 08:29.741
Mellie?

08:29.742 --> 08:31.675
I haven't talked to that girl
in a long time.

08:31.678 --> 08:34.613
Folks always ask, "why are you
still so loyal to her?"

08:34.615 --> 08:39.284
You know, after everything,
and i understand that. I do.

08:39.286 --> 08:40.919
But you know why?

08:40.921 --> 08:43.822
'cause she's family.

08:43.824 --> 08:45.757
And i always got her back.

08:45.759 --> 08:49.895
You tell her that for me, okay?
You tell her i got her back.

08:49.897 --> 08:53.532
And that her little sister
says hey.

08:53.534 --> 08:55.401
[ chuckles ]

08:55.402 --> 08:57.269
You should never have gone
to see her without telling me.

08:57.271 --> 08:59.771
Everyone has to be vetted,
including your sister.

08:59.773 --> 09:01.773
She was already through.
We had her vetted before.

09:01.775 --> 09:02.974
You weren't
the candidate before.

09:02.976 --> 09:04.826
You were the wife.

09:04.827 --> 09:06.677
And as long as you weren't
related to osama bin laden,

09:06.680 --> 09:08.780
No one gives a crap
what your family does.

09:08.782 --> 09:11.683
But even the dumbest american
can tell you about billy carter,

09:11.685 --> 09:13.752
Roger clinton,
every single bush,

09:13.754 --> 09:15.020
Every single kennedy.

09:15.022 --> 09:16.505
Fine. I get it.

09:16.506 --> 09:17.989
Mellie, she smiles.
She's polite.

09:17.991 --> 09:20.792
But right under the surface,
she is 50 shades of angry.

09:20.794 --> 09:21.977
I saw it.

09:21.978 --> 09:23.161
It would take
a top journalist

09:23.163 --> 09:25.230
Less than two days
to open her right up.

09:25.232 --> 09:26.782
Add in fame --

09:26.783 --> 09:28.333
If oprah showed up,
it would take 15 minutes.

09:28.335 --> 09:30.702
The damage she could do.

09:30.704 --> 09:31.903
Your sister --

09:31.905 --> 09:33.838
Half. Half sister.

09:33.840 --> 09:35.674
All you have to do
is look at her to know that.

09:35.676 --> 09:37.709
She looks exactly like her
trashy trailer-park mother.

09:37.711 --> 09:40.679
Harmony and i --

09:40.681 --> 09:43.281
My family,
there is an "us" and a "them."

09:43.283 --> 09:44.649
She is a "them."

09:44.651 --> 09:47.285
You want to make a run
for senator?

09:47.287 --> 09:50.221
You want to make a run
for the oval?

09:50.223 --> 09:54.225
You need to welcome her
into the fold with open arms.

09:54.227 --> 09:55.860
Make her an "us."

09:55.862 --> 09:59.230
[ sighs ]

09:59.232 --> 10:00.999
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

10:12.646 --> 10:14.613
[ buzzer ]

10:22.689 --> 10:23.688
[ sighs ]

10:23.690 --> 10:24.923
Who are you?

10:24.925 --> 10:26.925
My name is olivia pope.

10:26.927 --> 10:29.894
And for the next five minutes,
i'm your attorney.

10:29.896 --> 10:32.197
Don't need an attorney.
Well, you've got one.

10:32.199 --> 10:34.899
It's the only way we can
speak confidentially.
About...?

10:34.901 --> 10:36.935
About whether you really
committed the crime

10:36.937 --> 10:38.770
You're about to be
killed for.

10:38.772 --> 10:40.005
Your son
says you didn't.

10:40.007 --> 10:42.240
He says you feel guilty
because of what happened

10:42.242 --> 10:44.109
To your daughter
and that you're punishing --

10:44.111 --> 10:46.144
And punishing myself
by being here.

10:46.146 --> 10:47.846
Look, every three years
or so,

10:47.848 --> 10:50.248
He sends
one of you lawyer types my way,

10:50.250 --> 10:53.084
Tells you i'm innocent,
feeds you some sob story

10:53.086 --> 10:56.187
About me wanting to pay penance
for all the guilt i feel.

10:56.189 --> 10:58.924
It's garbage.

10:58.925 --> 11:01.660
I understand
how hard this is for him.

11:01.662 --> 11:03.662
He lost his whole family.

11:03.664 --> 11:05.430
But he needs to move on,

11:05.432 --> 11:08.933
Live his life,
stop worrying about mine.

11:08.935 --> 11:11.403
Convince him of that,
ms. Pope,

11:11.405 --> 11:14.906
You'll earn every penny
he's paying you.

11:14.908 --> 11:18.743
If you don't let me help you,
you're going to die for this.

11:23.817 --> 11:27.218
Let me tell you
something.

11:29.189 --> 11:31.990
Once you've stood
on an old dollhouse

11:31.992 --> 11:33.858
In your little girl's closet

11:33.860 --> 11:37.128
And tried to lift her
lifeless body up with one hand

11:37.130 --> 11:39.931
And loosen the noose
around her neck with the other,

11:39.933 --> 11:42.934
You're not alive anymore,
anyway.

11:51.078 --> 11:52.744
I'm taking your case.

11:52.746 --> 11:54.079
I'll fire you.
You can't.

11:54.081 --> 11:55.447
I work for your son.

11:55.449 --> 11:57.115
Look.
I believe you're innocent.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.317
I believe you didn't kill
dan hoffman.

11:59.319 --> 12:01.453
I believe
you don't deserve to die.

12:01.455 --> 12:02.987
And i'm gonna make sure

12:02.989 --> 12:05.156
You walk out of here
a free man.

12:05.158 --> 12:06.725
[ buzzer ]

12:18.472 --> 12:21.172
You know what this safe house
reminds me of?

12:21.174 --> 12:22.507
Brussels.

12:22.509 --> 12:24.843
Ugh. The worst.

12:24.845 --> 12:26.445
Brussels?
[ scoffs ]

12:26.446 --> 12:28.046
Try belfast for three years,
then see how you feel.

12:28.048 --> 12:30.882
I'm gonna need
your phones now.
Got it.

12:33.053 --> 12:35.153
That was liv.
She took the george reed case.

12:35.155 --> 12:37.455
We have a client.
I guess that means
i've got first watch.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.457
Who's up for charades?

12:40.894 --> 12:43.128
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

12:43.130 --> 12:44.996
Mellie's sister
is in town.

12:44.998 --> 12:47.065
Wait, harmony's in town.

12:47.067 --> 12:48.833
You need to keep her
away from the press.

12:48.835 --> 12:50.418
Okay.

12:50.419 --> 12:52.002
You will keep her away
from the press,

12:52.005 --> 12:53.805
But she will bring ruin
anyway!

12:53.807 --> 12:56.374
We're on the edge
of a great storm here.

12:56.376 --> 12:57.976
There's a strange wind.

12:57.978 --> 12:59.244
It's too warm.

12:59.246 --> 13:02.180
You know it's coming.
It's scary.

13:02.182 --> 13:06.017
But when that storm clears,
when harmony leaves,

13:06.019 --> 13:10.255
The sky will be bright,
and the world will be right,

13:10.257 --> 13:13.024
And we will find
little flowers

13:13.026 --> 13:15.093
Growing under the wreckage

13:15.095 --> 13:18.029
Because fitz
will no longer support

13:18.031 --> 13:21.065
Mellie's preposterous run
for the presidency.

13:21.067 --> 13:24.035
Team fitzmel or mellitz
or whatever the hell it is

13:24.037 --> 13:25.503
Will be over,

13:25.505 --> 13:28.239
Because if there is one thing
fitz hates --

13:28.241 --> 13:31.075
And i'm using
the word "hates" here --

13:31.077 --> 13:35.180
It's the messy, petty, bitchy
craziness that overtakes mellie

13:35.182 --> 13:38.016
When her dirty laundry
of a family

13:38.018 --> 13:40.051
Is exposed
to the open air.

13:40.053 --> 13:42.086
They will be done.

13:43.456 --> 13:46.057
[ groans ]

13:46.059 --> 13:49.260
Ma'am,
your sister is here.

13:49.262 --> 13:50.161
[ sighs ]

13:50.163 --> 13:51.930
Show her right in,
rachel.

13:52.599 --> 13:56.301
Well, mellie,
you got what you wanted.

13:56.303 --> 13:58.353
Here i am.

13:58.354 --> 14:00.404
[ chuckles ] harmony!
It's so good to see you!

14:00.407 --> 14:02.273
Welcome
to the white house.

14:02.275 --> 14:03.842
Thank you.

14:03.844 --> 14:05.176
Hello again, harmony.

14:05.178 --> 14:07.278
Oh, hey, liz.
[ laughs ]

14:07.280 --> 14:08.980
[ singsong voice ]
harmony.

14:08.982 --> 14:10.181
[ singsong voice ]
cyrus.

14:10.183 --> 14:12.283
You look...Festive.

14:12.285 --> 14:13.618
[ both chuckle ]

14:13.620 --> 14:15.920
How's it going
with that prostitute of yours

14:15.922 --> 14:17.021
You got mixed up with?

14:17.023 --> 14:17.622
We got married.

14:17.624 --> 14:19.991
Thanks for asking.

14:23.864 --> 14:24.863
Well...

14:24.865 --> 14:26.231
[ chuckles ]

14:26.232 --> 14:27.598
Uh, there'll be plenty of time
later for gabbing.

14:27.601 --> 14:29.934
Why don't we start off
by showing you around?

14:29.936 --> 14:31.369
Do you need to borrow
some flats?

14:31.371 --> 14:34.105
You got a problem
with my clothes?

14:34.107 --> 14:37.475
No. Of course not.
I just, um...

14:37.477 --> 14:40.545
It's a lot of walking,
that's all.

14:40.547 --> 14:43.882
Well, i walk all the time
in these.

14:43.884 --> 14:47.051
All right, so, we will get
started with the east wing.

14:47.053 --> 14:50.188
This is home, not just
to the first lady's office,

14:50.190 --> 14:53.491
But to the office of
the white house social secretary

14:53.493 --> 14:57.362
And the correspondence
department.

14:57.364 --> 14:59.330
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

14:59.332 --> 15:00.598
Harmony.

15:00.600 --> 15:01.499
Oh, my god.

15:01.501 --> 15:02.901
She makes soaps now.

15:02.903 --> 15:04.669
Cyrus must be loving this.

15:04.671 --> 15:07.205
He's like a storm chaser in
a van hurling down the highway,

15:07.207 --> 15:08.973
Face pressed up
against the windshield,

15:08.975 --> 15:10.508
Grinning wildly,

15:10.509 --> 15:12.042
Waiting for everything
to go to hell,

15:12.045 --> 15:13.912
Wanting to be there
when it does.

15:13.914 --> 15:15.414
I've been in that van.

15:15.415 --> 15:16.915
Anything new to report
on congressman reed?

15:16.917 --> 15:18.349
Not yet.

15:18.351 --> 15:20.018
You're gonna make us look bad,
aren't you?

15:20.020 --> 15:21.586
I hope so.

15:21.588 --> 15:24.389
George reed --
delaware inmate 789766,

15:24.391 --> 15:26.057
On death row since 1999.

15:26.059 --> 15:28.092
George became a single dad
to two kids,

15:28.094 --> 15:29.928
Nick and jamie, when his wife
died in a car crash.

15:29.930 --> 15:31.696
For a few years,
it seemed like they'd be okay

15:31.698 --> 15:34.399
Until jamie hanged herself
at 15.

15:34.401 --> 15:36.701
15.
Diary revealed she was sleeping
with her math teacher,

15:36.703 --> 15:37.568
Daniel hoffman.

15:37.570 --> 15:39.037
A real class act,

15:39.039 --> 15:40.972
That mr. "please, kids,
call me dan" hoffman.

15:40.974 --> 15:42.373
Only statuary raped jamie
for six months

15:42.375 --> 15:45.009
Before breaking her heart
under the bleachers.

15:45.011 --> 15:46.511
When jamie's diary
was discovered,

15:46.513 --> 15:48.112
George reed
went to the hoffman house

15:48.114 --> 15:50.715
And shot daniel hoffman
twice in the chest.

15:50.717 --> 15:53.017
I pointed the gun at his chest
and shot him twice,

15:53.019 --> 15:55.487
Maybe three times.

15:55.488 --> 15:57.956
Do you want to know what i would
have done if that was my kid?
Both: No.

15:57.958 --> 16:00.358
Did the police look into
other suspects, other leads?

16:00.360 --> 16:02.327
There was no investigation
because there was nothing

16:02.329 --> 16:03.995
To investigate --
the case was closed.

16:03.997 --> 16:06.130
Well, now it's open.
What about other girls?

16:06.132 --> 16:07.865
Teachers like dan hoffman,

16:07.866 --> 16:09.599
There's a good chance
jamie wasn't the first victim.

16:09.602 --> 16:11.035
I was 16.

16:11.037 --> 16:13.004
It was awful.
<i>He</i> was awful.

16:13.006 --> 16:15.673
As far as i'm concerned,
george reed is a hero.

16:15.675 --> 16:18.042
You've seen
the after-school special.

16:18.044 --> 16:20.044
A teenage girl falls
for the teacher who
makes her feel pretty.

16:20.046 --> 16:21.346
I was 15.
He was a predator.

16:21.348 --> 16:22.714
What else
do you need to know?

16:22.716 --> 16:24.182
That never happened.

16:24.184 --> 16:25.684
Are you sure?

16:25.685 --> 16:27.185
That would be a hard thing
to forget.

16:27.187 --> 16:30.021
You'd have to work hard
to forget something like that.

16:31.992 --> 16:34.092
Something
that never happened.

16:34.094 --> 16:37.495
Dan hoffman slept with at least
three other students.

16:37.497 --> 16:38.429
Huck: Probably more.

16:38.431 --> 16:39.497
Employment records show

16:39.499 --> 16:40.765
He moved
through four high schools

16:40.767 --> 16:42.717
In two states
in over six years.

16:42.718 --> 16:44.668
The creep.
Congressman, bigger picture --
there could have been

16:44.671 --> 16:47.105
A lot of other angry fathers
out there who wanted revenge.

16:47.107 --> 16:48.439
Or angry mothers.

16:48.441 --> 16:50.008
Or wives.

16:50.010 --> 16:52.310
Your husband changes jobs
so often,

16:52.312 --> 16:54.178
You're packing your bags
every year or two.

16:54.180 --> 16:55.780
How do you not know?
Or at least suspect?

16:55.782 --> 16:57.315
Track down
dan hoffman's ex-wife.

16:57.317 --> 16:58.483
I want to know
where she was

16:58.485 --> 17:00.051
The night
of her husband's murder.

17:00.053 --> 17:02.720
And i want
to interview her myself.

17:02.722 --> 17:04.522
[ doorbell rings ]

17:07.727 --> 17:09.494
Lisa hoffman?

17:09.496 --> 17:12.013
No. I'm her sister.

17:12.014 --> 17:14.531
I'm sorry, but lisa passed away
a couple of weeks ago.

17:17.270 --> 17:19.103
All right, i got all
the essentials for you
guys -- pizza pockets,

17:19.105 --> 17:21.506
Ice cream, cinnamon rolls,
toilet paper, a deck of cards,

17:21.508 --> 17:22.740
If anyone
wants to play killer.

17:22.742 --> 17:24.108
Get it?

17:27.680 --> 17:29.113
[ gasping ]

17:29.115 --> 17:30.181
Holy crap!

17:56.176 --> 17:58.176
[ gunshots ]

18:10.123 --> 18:11.789
It's one dinner,
fitz. Please.

18:11.791 --> 18:14.492
She's your sister, not mine.
You have dinner with the woman.

18:14.494 --> 18:15.994
She doesn't bite.

18:15.995 --> 18:17.495
Sir, the secretary of congress
will be here

18:17.497 --> 18:18.830
Any minute.
Mellie, are we done?

18:18.832 --> 18:19.797
Fitz.
Fine.

18:19.799 --> 18:21.399
[ groans ]

18:21.401 --> 18:24.202
Everything okay, sir?

18:24.204 --> 18:25.736
Harmony's
got her rattled.

18:25.738 --> 18:27.538
As far as setbacks go,
if she doesn't toughen up,

18:27.540 --> 18:28.840
She'll never make it
through a campaign,

18:28.842 --> 18:30.575
Whether i'm standing
by her side or not.

18:30.577 --> 18:33.744
Sir, secretary thompson
is here to see you.

18:33.746 --> 18:34.779
Send her in.

18:34.781 --> 18:36.681
Madam secretary.

18:36.683 --> 18:40.151
Good to see you.
Thanks for coming by.

18:40.153 --> 18:41.786
You're sure
this was ballard?

18:41.788 --> 18:44.455
In the middle of a fight,
your adrenaline's flowing.

18:44.457 --> 18:47.125
You want me to fight
you right now, see if
you remember my face?

18:47.127 --> 18:48.793
Something tells me you will.
Stand down, charlie.

18:48.795 --> 18:50.461
Okay.

18:50.463 --> 18:52.463
This didn't go as planned,

18:52.465 --> 18:56.300
So we find some other agents
who worked with jake.

18:56.302 --> 18:58.769
Oh, yeah, because once the other
agents hear about these guys,

18:58.771 --> 19:00.771
They'll just jump
at the chance, right, max?

19:00.773 --> 19:02.707
We got this, rosen.
You can go.

19:02.709 --> 19:04.208
Well, if you're sure.

19:06.846 --> 19:09.881
We got to kill jake.

19:09.883 --> 19:11.349
No way.

19:11.351 --> 19:12.584
Why not?

19:12.585 --> 19:13.818
Because mr. Peabody out there
said so?

19:13.820 --> 19:16.220
Or because if jake dies,
your boss will be sad?

19:16.222 --> 19:17.455
Trust me, robin.

19:17.456 --> 19:18.689
If we don't
take ballard out pronto,

19:18.691 --> 19:20.358
Somebody's gonna be
rolling us up next.

19:20.360 --> 19:22.860
It's two against one, charlie,
and i seriously doubt

19:22.862 --> 19:24.662
You can kill jake
without our help.

19:24.664 --> 19:26.931
Plus we have no idea
where he is, right, huck?

19:26.933 --> 19:28.233
Huck?

19:28.234 --> 19:29.534
Jake isn't jake
anymore, quinn.

19:29.536 --> 19:31.769
What are you
talking about?

19:31.771 --> 19:33.938
There's an explanation
for this.

19:33.940 --> 19:35.773
There has to be.
Jake is jake.

19:35.775 --> 19:37.875
Th-this is not jake.
It is.

19:37.877 --> 19:39.677
We were trained
the same way.

19:39.679 --> 19:42.280
We pushed him too far.
He's in survival mode.

19:42.282 --> 19:43.948
He's got to that place
where you don't think,

19:43.950 --> 19:45.616
Where it's just
your five senses,

19:45.618 --> 19:47.151
Where all you do is react,

19:47.152 --> 19:48.685
Where killing is as easy
as buttoning your shirt.

19:48.688 --> 19:50.888
I'm sorry.
Charlie's right.

19:50.890 --> 19:52.723
He has to be stopped.
There you go, buddy.

19:52.725 --> 19:54.559
Now you're talking.

19:54.561 --> 19:55.893
Your turn.
In or out?

19:55.895 --> 19:59.931
You heard him, robin.
Ballard's gone mad dog.

19:59.933 --> 20:01.933
We find him
and put a bullet in his head.

20:11.411 --> 20:14.579
In.

20:14.581 --> 20:16.514
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

20:20.853 --> 20:21.852
Quinn: Hi, liv.

20:21.854 --> 20:23.387
Quinn, where are you?

20:23.389 --> 20:25.289
Drugstore.
Tampon run.

20:25.291 --> 20:26.591
Lisa hoffman is dead.

20:26.593 --> 20:27.825
What happened?

20:27.827 --> 20:28.993
Pancreatic cancer.

20:28.995 --> 20:31.429
Her sister deborah
is packing up her house

20:31.431 --> 20:32.864
As we speak.

20:32.865 --> 20:34.298
Lisa hoffman
wasn't a career criminal,

20:34.300 --> 20:36.867
Which means if she murdered
her husband 15 years ago,

20:36.869 --> 20:38.502
She might have left
some evidence.

20:38.504 --> 20:40.571
And that evidence is probably
somewhere in her house.

20:40.573 --> 20:42.740
Okay, we're on it.

20:44.877 --> 20:46.877
So, that's it?

20:46.879 --> 20:49.614
You hit a couple keys,
you track down jake,

20:49.616 --> 20:53.417
And we kill him -- jake,

20:53.419 --> 20:55.953
The guy who did everything
he could to rescue olivia.

20:57.523 --> 20:59.857
Maybe you won't
be able to find him.

20:59.859 --> 21:02.693
Maybe he'll disappear,
never come back,

21:02.695 --> 21:04.996
And -- and we won't
have to kill him.

21:04.998 --> 21:07.431
I can still use the cell towers
to triangulate his position.

21:07.433 --> 21:08.833
We'll have him
as soon as his cell signal

21:08.835 --> 21:11.002
Connects
with the three towers.

21:14.907 --> 21:17.775
Oh, finally.
She's leaving.

21:17.777 --> 21:21.012
Let's go.

21:22.949 --> 21:26.350
Olivia:
We're looking for anything
that can clear george reed

21:26.352 --> 21:28.786
And implicate lisa hoffman
in the murder of her husband --

21:28.788 --> 21:30.788
E-mails, letters, diaries,

21:30.790 --> 21:33.624
Bank statements, wills,
life-insurance policies.

21:33.626 --> 21:34.759
Nothing.

21:34.761 --> 21:36.861
Nothing here, either.

21:36.863 --> 21:37.962
[ sighs ]

21:37.964 --> 21:40.298
Let's try the basement.

21:58.418 --> 22:01.485
I think
i got something.

22:01.487 --> 22:02.386
Yeah?

22:02.388 --> 22:03.888
Oh, yeah.
What is it?

22:03.890 --> 22:05.856
Gun.

22:05.858 --> 22:07.658
Same make and caliber
as the murder weapon.

22:07.660 --> 22:09.694
Huck: Lisa could have used it
to shoot her husband.

22:09.696 --> 22:10.928
At the very least,
reasonable doubt.

22:10.930 --> 22:12.630
George reed
isn't in the clear yet.

22:12.632 --> 22:13.964
Not until we have
a ballistics report

22:13.966 --> 22:18.002
That can definitively tie
that gun to the murder.

22:18.004 --> 22:20.071
We can't bag it and send it off
for independent testing.

22:20.073 --> 22:21.939
Because we'll never be able to
prove chain of custody.

22:21.941 --> 22:24.875
But if we throw the cops
an anonymous tip,

22:24.877 --> 22:26.744
We're letting them
prove chain of custody.

22:26.746 --> 22:28.779
Don't touch that gun.

22:28.781 --> 22:30.481
[ siren chirps ]

22:37.590 --> 22:39.890
Liv really believes
this guy is innocent.

22:39.892 --> 22:40.891
She's testing
her gut again.

22:40.893 --> 22:42.360
I hope it's working
this time.

22:42.362 --> 22:43.728
[ beeps ]

22:43.729 --> 22:45.095
What was that?
The tracking software.

22:45.098 --> 22:47.832
A tower on canal just picked up
jake's cell signal.

22:47.834 --> 22:50.101
We got him.

22:53.873 --> 22:56.807
See, that's how
i got into soapmaking --

22:56.809 --> 22:58.909
'cause daddy always said
it was important

22:58.911 --> 23:00.478
To use
all parts of the animal.

23:00.480 --> 23:01.712
You remember that, mel?

23:01.714 --> 23:03.948
Or was he not hunting much
when he was married

23:03.950 --> 23:05.583
To your mama?
Oh, i don't recall.

23:05.585 --> 23:06.784
What are they made from?

23:06.786 --> 23:08.886
Mostly deer fat,
sometimes a little duck.

23:08.888 --> 23:11.122
Of course, if i don't have
anything else on hand,

23:11.124 --> 23:12.957
I'll just use
plain old bacon.

23:12.959 --> 23:14.091
[ both chuckle ]

23:14.093 --> 23:15.943
See here,

23:15.944 --> 23:17.794
Fitz, whoever trimmed this,
they did a real good job.

23:17.797 --> 23:20.631
There's probably a bunch of fat
that's just being wasted.

23:20.633 --> 23:23.768
I should have talked
to that fancy chef of yours

23:23.770 --> 23:26.470
Back there
and had him save me a bucket.

23:26.472 --> 23:28.906
[ both chuckle ]
well, i hate to change
the subject, but --

23:28.908 --> 23:30.841
Mellie!

23:30.843 --> 23:33.477
Fitz and i are talking
about my soaps.
I know that,

23:33.479 --> 23:35.980
But we've been discussing
your soaps all night. I just --

23:35.982 --> 23:37.648
You just don't like to talk
about something

23:37.650 --> 23:39.083
That doesn't have
anything to do with you.

23:39.085 --> 23:40.985
[ both chuckle ]

23:40.987 --> 23:43.621
See, this is what
my sister does, fitz.

23:43.623 --> 23:44.789
For the love of...

23:44.791 --> 23:46.791
It's "mr. President,"
harmony.

23:46.793 --> 23:48.893
What?

23:48.895 --> 23:50.694
I have been sitting here
listening to you call

23:50.696 --> 23:52.062
The leader of the free world
by his nickname

23:52.064 --> 23:54.064
When it is not "fitz" to you.

23:54.066 --> 23:55.833
It is "mr. President."

23:55.835 --> 23:57.935
So, just show
a little respect.

23:57.937 --> 23:59.136
Mellie.

23:59.138 --> 24:01.906
You want to tell me
about respect?

24:01.908 --> 24:04.041
Oh, that is rich,
mellie.

24:04.043 --> 24:07.111
What the hell do you know
about respect?

24:07.113 --> 24:08.746
I know that the president
of the united states

24:08.748 --> 24:11.115
Has better things to worry about
than these ridiculous soaps

24:11.116 --> 24:13.483
That you are making
out of dead animals.
Okay, see, this is what you used
to do to me when i was little.

24:13.486 --> 24:15.970
All right.
You're trying to make me
feel small.

24:15.971 --> 24:18.455
You're trying to take things
away from me.
What about what you
took away from me?

24:18.458 --> 24:21.125
See, first, it was my family,
and now it is my soaps.
They are not your family.

24:21.127 --> 24:23.894
How could they be when you're
trying to turn them against me?

24:23.896 --> 24:25.496
You know what?
You think you're better than me.

24:25.498 --> 24:26.864
I<i> am</i> better than you.
Really?

24:26.866 --> 24:28.216
Why, mellie?

24:28.217 --> 24:29.567
Why? 'cause you live
in this great big house?

24:29.569 --> 24:31.235
'cause you're on the cover
of magazines?

24:31.237 --> 24:33.904
Because i don't embarrass myself
everywhere that i go.

24:33.906 --> 24:36.006
Because i have
a semblance of class.

24:36.008 --> 24:37.608
Okay, i could give
a rat's ass about --

24:37.610 --> 24:39.093
Because i wasn't raised

24:39.094 --> 24:40.577
By that home-wrecking whore
you call a mother!

24:40.580 --> 24:42.813
Okay, that's enough.
Okay, you know what?
That is it.

24:42.815 --> 24:44.548
Lord knows daddy
never would have strayed

24:44.550 --> 24:46.650
If your frigid mama
hadn't run him out of the house.

24:46.652 --> 24:48.152
You know, i bet there's
a whole lot of people

24:48.154 --> 24:50.754
Would be real interested
in that story.

24:50.756 --> 24:52.857
I wonder
who i should ring first.

24:52.859 --> 24:55.025
You know, i always loved me
that katie couric.

24:55.027 --> 24:56.927
All right,
i said that's enough!

25:02.835 --> 25:05.236
You better watch
how you speak to me.

25:05.238 --> 25:06.937
Dirt i got on you, sis...

25:06.939 --> 25:08.639
[ chuckles ]

25:08.641 --> 25:11.775
It could come in real handy
one day.

25:19.085 --> 25:20.851
[<i> camera shutter clicking</i> ]

25:20.853 --> 25:22.219
Do you see jake?
Charlie: Nope.

25:22.221 --> 25:23.921
I'm right where you sent me,
huck. I don't see anything.

25:23.923 --> 25:25.923
You sure
this gizmo of yours works?

25:25.925 --> 25:28.025
Huck: It works,
but the triangulation

25:28.027 --> 25:29.927
Is only accurate
to a couple of square blocks.

25:29.929 --> 25:31.829
When he moves,
i can get a new data point

25:31.831 --> 25:33.464
And i can narrow the search.
Hold on.

25:33.465 --> 25:35.098
How sad were you
when radioshack went under?

25:35.101 --> 25:36.567
Did you cry?
Be honest.

25:36.569 --> 25:37.935
What if he's
done moving?

25:37.937 --> 25:39.570
He'll move.

25:41.040 --> 25:42.907
Come on. Come on.

25:45.811 --> 25:46.677
Look.

25:46.679 --> 25:48.045
What?

25:48.047 --> 25:49.914
Do you know
where he is?

25:49.916 --> 25:51.749
Oh, my god,
that's liv's building.

25:51.751 --> 25:53.584
Okay, can you access
her security system?

25:54.587 --> 25:56.921
Got it. That's the camera
outside her front door.

25:56.923 --> 25:58.122
Is he already
inside her apartment?

25:58.124 --> 25:59.590
Call her now.

25:59.591 --> 26:01.057
Sorry, charlie,
got to go.

26:03.262 --> 26:05.262
It's ringing.

26:05.264 --> 26:06.263
Ringing.

26:06.265 --> 26:08.132
Voicemail.
Damn it!

26:08.134 --> 26:09.800
We have to get
over there now.

26:25.284 --> 26:27.618
You're not
gonna like it.

